# C++ Calculator

A menu-driven console calculator built while learning core C++ fundamentals. This project performs basic arithmetic operations along with modulus and power calculation using functions, loops, switch-case, and input validation.

## Features
- Addition
- Subtraction
- Multiplication
- Division (with division-by-zero handling)
- Modulus
- Power calculation
- Menu-driven interface
- Continuous operation until user exits

## Concepts Practiced
- Functions
- Switch-case statements
- While loops
- User input/output
- Conditional logic
- Basic error handling

## Technologies Used
- C++
- Standard Library (`iostream`)

## How to Run
1. Compile the program:
```bash
g++ calculator.cpp -o calculator
